    <title ixia_locid="55" class="- topic/title ">Editing Interface Settings</title>
    <shortdesc ixia_locid="56" class="- topic/shortdesc ">You can change the settings for a host interface.</shortdesc>
    <prolog class="- topic/prolog ">
        <author ixia_locid="57" class="- topic/author ">Jim Owens</author>
    </prolog>
    <taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody ">
        <context id="context_N1001E_N1001B_N10001" ixia_locid="58" class="- topic/section task/context ">
            <p ixia_locid="59" class="- topic/p ">The ability to change the interface settings is especially useful for
                updating the management interface. When a compute node is first created, its
                management interface is automatically set up using the default
                    <nameliteral ixia_locid="70" class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b wr-sw-d/nameliteral ">Interface Type</nameliteral> (<nameliteral ixia_locid="71" class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b wr-sw-d/nameliteral ">ethernet</nameliteral>).
                If you are using LAG on the management network, you must update this manually to
                    <nameliteral ixia_locid="72" class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b wr-sw-d/nameliteral ">aggregated ethernet</nameliteral>.</p>
            <p ixia_locid="82" class="- topic/p ">You can also edit a management or infrastructure interface to attach
                to a data network by selecting <uicontrol ixia_locid="83" class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">data</uicontrol> as an
                additional Network Type for the interface, or using the CLI. For CLI instructions,
                see <xref href="jow1427029415968.xml" ixia_locid="86" class="- topic/xref "/>.</p>
            <p ixia_locid="90" class="- topic/p "><draft-comment author="jowens" ixia_locid="91" translate="no" dir="ltr" class="- topic/draft-comment ">US62814 added</draft-comment>To add or edit IP
                addresses on a data interface, see the <cite ixia_locid="92" class="- topic/cite ">HP Helion OpenStack Carrier Grade Administration Guide:
                    Adding an IP Address to a Data Interface</cite>.</p>
        </context>
        <steps class="- topic/ol task/steps ">
            <step id="step_N1003F_N1003C_N1001F_N10001" ixia_locid="73" class="- topic/li task/step " conref="jow1426453628262.xml#jow1426453628262/lock_host">
                <cmd ixia_locid="74" class="- topic/ph task/cmd "/>
            </step>
            <step id="step_N10048_N1003C_N1001F_N10001" ixia_locid="75" class="- topic/li task/step " conref="jow1426453628262.xml#jow1426453628262/open_details_locked_host">
                <cmd ixia_locid="76" class="- topic/ph task/cmd "/>
            </step>
            <step id="step_N10069_N10028_N1001C_N10001" ixia_locid="20" class="- topic/li task/step ">
                <cmd ixia_locid="21" class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Select the<uicontrol ixia_locid="22" class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "> Interfaces</uicontrol>
                    tab to display the existing interfaces.</cmd>
                <info ixia_locid="87" class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
                    <fig id="fig_N10076_N10073_N10064_N1004B_N1001F_N10001" ixia_locid="88" class="- topic/fig ">
                        <image alt="Interfaces list" href="rst1440770718462.image" ixia_locid="89" width="5.5in" placement="inline" class="- topic/image "/>
                    </fig>
                </info>
            </step>
            <step id="step_N1009A_N10027_N1001B_N10001" ixia_locid="60" class="- topic/li task/step ">
                <cmd ixia_locid="61" class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Click <uicontrol ixia_locid="62" class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Edit Interface</uicontrol> for the interface you want to
                    change.</cmd>
                <info ixia_locid="63" class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
                    <fig id="fig_xfz_5fm_vp" ixia_locid="64" class="- topic/fig ">
                        <image href="jow1426954976474.image" id="image_w5l_tlk_lr" ixia_locid="24" placement="inline" class="- topic/image ">
                            <alt ixia_locid="85" class="- topic/alt ">TiS Edit Interface</alt>
                        </image>
                    </fig>
                    <!-- p>If you are changing the <nameliteral>Interface Type</nameliteral> to
                            <nameliteral>aggregated ethernet</nameliteral>, select the second port
                        connected to the network.</p -->
                    <!-- JO 2015-03-24 screenshot? sounds plausible, but I don't see a second port -->
                </info>
            </step>
            <step id="step_N100BB_N10027_N1001B_N10001" ixia_locid="67" class="- topic/li task/step ">
                <cmd ixia_locid="68" class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Make the required changes, and then click <uicontrol ixia_locid="69" class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Save</uicontrol>.</cmd>
                <info ixia_locid="79" class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
                    <p ixia_locid="80" class="- topic/p ">The settings shown depend on the interface type. For
                        information about the available settings, see <xref href="jow1426955886080.xml" ixia_locid="81" class="- topic/xref "/>.</p>
                </info>
            </step>
            <step id="step_N100B2_N1003C_N1001F_N10001" ixia_locid="77" class="- topic/li task/step ">
                <cmd ixia_locid="78" class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Unlock the host.</cmd>
            </step>
        </steps>
